JUST as foreign media outlets raise alert on the possibility of Volcanic Eruption at Mount Oldonyo Lengai, the planned Loliondo-Serengeti Marathon, which is scheduled to take place near the so-called ‘Mountain of God,’ is ready to make scene of its own. And, this Saturday will see the sophomore installment of the Liliondo-Serengeti Marathon raising dust, or skidding in the mud of the remote Loliondo Division with some 500 athletes in tow. The second edition of the forthcoming race is probably going to be the holiday sporting event to sum up this year in athletics in the Northern Zone, where the threateningly active volcanic mountain of God to prominently feature. Coming up next weekend, the main event, clocking at 21 kilometres Half-Marathon, has so far attracted 500 runners and will be held in the remote Loliondo Division of Ngorongoro District, starting from Wasso all the way to Loliondo via Sakala. There will be auxiliary races mapped within the Loliondo-Serengeti Marathon including the 10 kilometres as well as the 5 kilometres’ events, according to Paulo Dudui the event coordinator, who explained that the main agenda of the athletics event is to promote the sport among farmers and livestock keepers. “We also intend to boost domestic tourism in the circuit covering Lake Natron, Ngorongoro Crater and the Volcanic Oldonyo L’engai Mountain as well as part of the Serengeti corridor mapped within Loliondo,” said Dudui, adding that the registration for those wishing to compete in event is free. “People can register online or via email and those who are within precinct can enrol at the Athletics Association (AA), the Regional Athletics office in Arusha or District Athletics Office in Loliondo,” he said. Dudui also said that the race aimed at promoting conservation efforts among the Sonjo farmers and Maasai livestock keepers, who live in the Serengeti Ecosystem, which covers the Maswa Game Reserve, Ngorongoro Conservation, Serengeti National Park, Loliondo Game Reserve and the Maasai-Mara reserve of Kenya. Runners will be chasing the remote wind while also contemplating the lucrative 10m/- of planned awards and prizes.